    "updated_at": "2015-12-30T09:15:15Z",
    "body": "@KeitIG Glad my app helped you! It's basically the same as the documentation except that the renderer sends IPC to the main to bring up a context menu, thus not blocking the renderer. For future viewers of this issue:\nIn your renderer process:\n\n``` js\nconst ipcRenderer = require('electron').ipcRenderer;\nvar template = /* Some menu template */\n\nwindow.addEventListener('contextmenu', function (e) {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    ipcRenderer.send('context-menu', template);\n}, false);\n```\n\nMain process:\n\n``` js\nconst electron = require('electron');\nconst Menu = electron.Menu;\nconst ipcMain = electron.ipcMain;\n\nipcMain.on('context-menu', function(event, template) {\n    var contextMenu = Menu.buildFromTemplate(template);\n    contextMenu.popup(mainWindow);\n });\n```\n"
  },
